File: A general view of the headquarters of the embattled South African main electricity provider Eskom. AFP/Gianluigi Guercia JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will reduce load-shedding to Stage 1 starting at 6am until 11pm on Sunday. Eskom said this is due to the recovery of generation reserves. READ: Eskom says gross debt increased to R488bn as of March "It is necessary to continue with load-shedding in order to fully recover the emergency generation reserves in preparation for the coming week," read a statement from the power utility. Eskom is urging customers to use electricity sparingly.